Root cause of frontend not built: rust-embed in Bazel exec root.

The genrule creates frontend/build/ in the real filesystem (pwd -P follows symlinks),
but the server compilation resolves ../../frontend/build/ through the exec root.
On CI, the exec root may not use directory symlinks for packages with BUILD.bazel,
so the side-effect build/ directory is invisible to the compiler.

Key evidence:
- Empty frontend/build/ compiles OK but embeds zero files (confirmed)
- Local clean build works because exec root uses dir symlinks locally
- CI release DMG binary returns "frontend not built" (confirmed via curl on x64 DMG)
- strings check was initially misleading (doctype is lowercase in SvelteKit)

Fix approach: build frontend before Bazel in CI, add filegroup to glob build/**
as compile_data so Bazel makes the files available as proper inputs.

Rejected: changing tauri.conf.json beforeBuildCommand paths (red herring — Tauri
window loads from localhost, not frontendDist).
